<bdy>

The prize is given for outstanding papers on the principles of distributed computing, whose significance and impact on the theory and/or practice of distributed computing has been evident for at least a decade. The Prize includes an award of $2000. <p>

The Prize is sponsored jointly by the ACM Symposium on Principles of Distributed Computing (PODC) and the <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../917/19495917.xml">
International Symposium on Distributed Computing</link> (<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../917/19495917.xml">
DISC</link>). This award is presented annually, with the presentation taking place alternately at ACM PODC and <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../917/19495917.xml">
DISC</link>.</p>
<p>

For the first three years, the prize was called the PODC Influential Paper Award.</p>

